{
  "If F'(x) = 3x^2 and F(1) = 5, then F(3) =": "",
  "26": "",
  "31": "",
  "32": "",
  "27": "",
  "F(3) = F(1) + integral from 1 to 3 of 3x^2 dx = 5 + [x^3] from 1 to 3 = 5 + (27 - 1) = 31.": "",
  "A particle moves with velocity v(t) = t^2 - 6t + 8. The particle changes direction at:": "",
  "t = 2 and t = 4": "",
  "t = 1 and t = 5": "",
  "t = 0 and t = 6": "",
  "t = 3 only": "",
  "The particle changes direction when v(t) = 0 and the sign of v changes: t^2 - 6t + 8 = (t-2)(t-4) = 0 at t = 2 and t = 4. Since v changes sign at both, these are direction-change points.": "",
  "Evaluate integral from 0 to 2 of |x - 1| dx.": "",
  "0": "",
  "2": "",
  "1/2": "",
  "1": "",
  "Split at x = 1: integral from 0 to 1 of (1-x) dx + integral from 1 to 2 of (x-1) dx = [x - x^2/2] from 0 to 1 + [x^2/2 - x] from 1 to 2 = (1 - 1/2) + (2 - 2 - 1/2 + 1) = 1/2 + 1/2 = 1.": "",
  "A tank starts with 200 liters. Water enters at 5 liters/min and exits at 3 liters/min. After 30 minutes, the tank contains:": "",
  "260 liters": "",
  "350 liters": "",
  "200 liters": "",
